      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-09-19T14:21:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Okay, turns out that this won\u0027t work due to the necessary flow. I changed GetTaskSpec to perform the lock itself and removed the cache\u0027s Lock and Unlock methods. I\u0027ll worry about the locking being slow later if it\u0027s necessary.",
      "parentUuid": "10261bad_ca535308",
      "revId": "c3af601e376c250db0d19a7b86a877ef111689e5",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "10261bad_0afcab9c",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/scheduling/specs.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 253,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-09-19T14:40:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok, sorry to be a pain. Internal locking is convenient when it works, but I definitely prefer external locking rather than a hybrid approach. It just gets too confusing.\n\nAnother possible approach is copy-on-write.",
      "parentUuid": "10261bad_6ae0bf1f",
      "revId": "c3af601e376c250db0d19a7b86a877ef111689e5",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
